column2: currentInitMemory        Initial memory the vm requested from the operating system for this pool
column3: currentMaxMemory        The maximum amount of memory this pool can have in bytes.
column4: currentUsedMemory        The estimated amount of used memory currently in use for this pool, measured in bytes.
column5: currentCommittedMemory        The amount of committed memory for this pool, measured in bytes.
column6: collectionUsedMemory        The estimated amount of used memory after that last garbage collection of this pool, measured in bytes.
column7: collectionUsageThreshold        The collection usage threshold for this pool in bytes
column8: collectionUsageExceeded        Total number of times the garbage collector detected that memory usage in this pool exceeded the collectionUsageThreshold
column9: usageThreshold        The usage threshold for this pool in bytes
column10: usageExceeded        Total number of times that memory usage in this pool exceeded the usageThreshold
